There are skilled tips for reconnaissance.

1.whoiis:
It's for searching the dns server-name,register, manage staff, technical staff and registration for the target.
1-1.terminal command:whois {the domain name of the target} -h {whois_server_ip}
1-2.Online whois resources:
https://who.is/
https://www.whois.com/whois/

2.Google Hacking:
It's a skill for searching public information about the target by google browser.
2-1.site:{the domain of the target}
2-2.site:{the domain of the target} filetype:txt/html
2-3.intitile:"index of" "parent directory"--->could find the web server resources
2-4.Online Google Hacking resources:
https://www.exploit-db.com/google-hacking-database
https://dorksearch.com/

3.Netcraft:
It's a skill for searching the frontend/backend skills of the target.
3-1.Online Netcraft resources:
https://searchdns.netcraft.com/

4.Shodan:
It's also a skill for searching the public information about the target's domain.
4-1.Online Shodan resources:
https://www.shodan.io/--->In this platform, if u input,'hostname {the target's domain}', then click 'view
report', you could get as much as information.

5.Dumpster:
It's a skill for searching the DNS record of the target's domain.
5-1.Online Dumpster resources:
https://dnsdumpster.com/

6.Web Wappalyzer:
It's a skill for searching the information of the web server.
6-1.Online Web Wappalyzer resources:
https://www.wappalyzer.com/

7.exiftool:
This tool is for searching the metadata of the target's file.
7-1.terminal command:exiftool -a -u {the target's file}
                                                                
